Ntuli was speaking at her rally in Durban on Saturday, which is part of her campaign for the party's top job. JOHANNESBURG - Democratic Alliance (DA) candidate leader Mbali Ntuli said to build a fair DA, the party must end the personality cults around leaders. Ntuli was speaking at her rally in Durban on Saturday, which is part of her campaign for the party's top job. She's calling for change in the organisation, which she said was in a deep crisis. Ntuli said her priority was to improve service delivery with the aim of restoring voter confidence. “We need to make people feel more included in our structures, we’re going to bring back fairness and no more victimisation as well as an end to personality cults around leaders.”